texts.text: *Cackle* My blood ran cold when I heard I was found out.
>As the Divine target Rahab, they're assaulted by demons.
Well done, demon residents. To thank you...
H-Heh... Rahab isn't to be taken lightly...
Still, I have no regrets. I wouldn't work with angels...
Their mutual foe is right before their eyes, yet look at them!
They sow enough chaos without me!
Yes. Instead of an alliance, they're at each other's throats...
We can't fight Rahab like this.
You're right. Otherwise Rahab will invade the world above.
We must stop him at all costs!
Rahab! You'll terrorize my kingdom no further!
Cait Sith! Please, join the angels just for now—
I've already cut down...every angel here.
The Divine may be gone, but I am still your strength!
>Meanwhile, behind Rahab and opposite Cait Sith and the others—
Cait Sith... He's fighting over there.
Wait for me! I'm on my wa—
It looks like that was the last demon in the area.
Thanks to those demons, my Divine army is in tatters.
As Weapons of God, fight until your dying breath!
>Camael cuts through the sky toward Rahab.
>As they slowly chip away at him,
Yes... Our demon allies are worse for wear, but they'll survive.
Most of the angels and demon solo fighters were wiped out.
Your fate was sealed the moment I noticed your scheme.
Camael, it's up to you to finish him off...
Come, Rahab! It is time for your final judgement!
>Camael rises into the sky for a death blow.
>However, a demon leaps into action at the same time.
Yeah, but this is bad! Look!
>It's the perfect chance to defeat Rahab,
>but Camael and Cait Sith are frozen in a deadlock.
"If I attack Rahab, he'll attack me."
My plan may have failed, but luck is still on my side.
I'm beggin' ya! Work together just this once!
You will rue your grievous actions today.
